HEADWORD: Glycosine
<hw>Gly"co*sine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An organic base, <chform>C6H6N4</chform>, produced artificially as
a white, crystalline powder, by the action of ammonia on
glyoxal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

